courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of this course, students will be able to:

* Understand the fundamental concepts and roles of sensor systems in Earth, space, and astronomical observation;
* Explain how different physical environments influence sensor design, performance, and limitations;
* Interpret sensor data with awareness of uncertainty, noise, and measurement constraints;
* Compare and evaluate sensor options based on mission objectives and system-level trade-offs;
* Apply system-level thinking to propose sensor configurations for Earth observation and space missions.
